The paper deals with a protocol for secure communication and authentication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of location and user attributes also suggests a potential connection to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of encryption and attribute-based encryption, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS).
